label chapter19:

    # [Scene: Glasshouse Lab & Seedbank | Night — immediate after municipal hall advisory]

    scene bg ch14_f99e88_1 at full_bg
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: Distant municipal sirens; the hum of standby generators; the wet slap of boots on metal grating]
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Rapid, discordant strings — a frantic pulse rising]
    "You come awake to a different kind of silence — not quiet, but the kind that presses in when too many alarms are working at once. Mika's message is a physical thing in your pocket; the"
    "live gauge on his tablet feels like a wound you can't stop touching. You left the municipal hall on a break-you-won't-rest kind of breath and ran here because this is the place that breathes for everyone"
    "else — the seedbank, the samples, the protocols that might let Laurel Bay begin again if the worst comes."
    "You slam open the outer door. The smell hits you first: warm humidity, salt, the sharp chemical tang of iodine wipes and ethanol from rushed sterilizations, and beneath it, the bitter edge of adrenaline. Inside, the glasshouse is a hive of motion."
    show mika_tran at left:
        zoom 0.7

    mika_tran "You good? The feed's still spiking. We—"
    "he holds up his tablet; his fingers are clumsy with gloves"
    show marina_reyes at right:
        zoom 0.7

    marina_reyes "Show me the back-ups. Which trays are priority?"

    mika_tran "All of them. The cryptic cultures are on bench three—"
    "he stops, breath ragged"

    mika_tran "—we only have partial cold-chain if the power goes."
    "Kaori 'Kai' Matsuda pushes through behind you, neon braid whipping, eyes like flint in the green light."
    show kaori_kai_matsuda at center:
        zoom 0.7

    kaori_kai_matsuda "Okay, no. We're not babysitting beakers while people move out. We can rig floating rigs faster than the council can order sandbags. Pulling samples—"

    marina_reyes "We keep the samples. If we lose the seedbank, we don't come back. We lose the thing that makes coming back possible."

    kaori_kai_matsuda "That's cowardice depending on which side of the barricade you're standing on."
    "The words surge up like cold water. Kai's accusation lands with the force of gale wind. The glasshouse hum becomes a roar in your ears. You can feel your pulse in your throat."
    "Amalia arrives last, cheeks flushed, clipboard clutched like a talisman. Her voice trembles in a way you haven't heard from her before."
    hide mika_tran
    show amalia_reyes at left:
        zoom 0.7

    amalia_reyes "People are asking where to go. My lists—people with mobility issues, pets, elderly—"

    marina_reyes "We'll route them to the school gym first. Mika, can you get the gen set to full load? Kaori, I need you on the flats to start untying the test-lines—careful with the water rigs—"

    kaori_kai_matsuda "You want me to untie the thing I begged you to champion?"

    marina_reyes "I want the long-term to live."
    "Kai looks as if you'll bitten her. For a moment she says nothing and the green light makes her braid a comet."
    hide marina_reyes
    hide kaori_kai_matsuda
    hide amalia_reyes

    scene bg ch14_f99e88_2 at full_bg
    "Kai doesn't move immediately. She folds her arms and stares at you with a face that says: you chose. There's something like betrayal written in the set of her jaw. Your chest tightens."
    show marina_reyes at left:
        zoom 0.7

    marina_reyes "If we don't have the seeds, we can't rebuild the beds, Kaori. We can't replant the long-lines from memory."
    show kaori_kai_matsuda at right:
        zoom 0.7

    kaori_kai_matsuda "If we stay to seal jars while everyone evacuates, you'll have preserved slides and samples while our neighbors drown."

    marina_reyes "I am not choosing jars over people. I'm choosing the thing that will let people come home."
    "There are no perfect words. There is only the wedge between them: the short, immediate imperative to act in the street, and the cold, stubborn logic of preserving what can be used after the water recedes."

    menu:
        "Call Elias Kato and ask for municipal transport":
            "You fumble for his number, thumb hovering: the call will complicate more than it helps, but his trucks and the council's authorization could move cold boxes faster."
        "Rally the volunteers here now":
            "You look up at the small circle of faces — Mika, Amalia, two grad-students — and the truth hits: this place runs on people who show up at three in the morning. You begin to shout names."

    # --- merge ---
    "Scene continues"
    "Mika moves like a machine with a human heartbeat — efficient, breathless."
    show mika_tran at center:
        zoom 0.7

    mika_tran "Generator's on diesel reserve. I can cycle pumps to conserve, but the humidity controllers will stall if we cut too much."

    marina_reyes "Prioritize the cryo-bank and the labeled spore-cases. Hatchlings and the live cultures get emergency vials—double-wrap, then into the insulated crates. Amalia, secure the manifests. Kaori, when you come back from the flats, we catalogue everything we send out."
    "You aren't asking. You are ordering because there isn't time for consensus. Your buoy pendant rubs cold beneath your shirt, a small, stubborn weight that keeps you tethered to the father you lost and to the promise you whispered under the glasshouse light: keep the seeds. Keep the knowledge."
    hide marina_reyes
    hide kaori_kai_matsuda
    hide mika_tran

    scene bg ch14_f99e88_3 at full_bg
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: The clack of clasps; the sharp tear of packing tape; distant shouts from outside]
